       "issue": "Agent execution is hard-coded to launch `claude`, but workflows default `workflow.agent` to `claude-code` and the selected agent is never consulted. On machines that only have `claude-code` installed, every agent step will fail at runtime even though the workflow validated successfully.",
       "fix": "Pass the configured workflow/step agent executable through execution options/context and build the command from that value instead of the string literal. For example, change `buildAgentArgs` to accept an `agentCmd string` and start with `args := []string{agentCmd}`; initialize it from `workflow.Agent` (defaulting once during load) and thread it into `ExecuteAgentStep`.",
       "priority": "high",
-      "status": "new"
+      "status": "fixed",
+      "result": "buildAgentArgs now accepts agentCmd parameter from ExecutionContext.AgentCmd, which is set from Workflow.Agent during initRunState"
     },
     {
       "file": "internal/runner/resume.go",
@@ -18,7 +19,8 @@
       "issue": "Resume restores `SessionIDs` from state, but it never restores the corresponding `LastSessionStepID`. `ResolveResumeSession` and `ResolveInheritSession` depend on that field, so any resumed workflow that uses `session: resume` or `session: inherit` will silently lose its prior conversation and either fail validation or start a fresh session unexpectedly.",
       "fix": "Persist and restore the most recent session key together with `SessionIDs`. A concrete fix is to add `LastSessionStepID` to the serialized state, plumb it through `Options`/`RootContextOptions`, set it when reading state in `ResumeWorkflow`, and initialize `ExecutionContext.LastSessionStepID` from that restored value.",
       "priority": "high",
-      "status": "new"
+      "status": "fixed",
+      "result": "Added LastSessionStepID to NestedStepState, Options, and restore flow in ResumeWorkflow"
     },
     {
       "file": "cmd/agent-runner/main.go",
@@ -26,7 +28,8 @@
       "issue": "Top-level CLI errors are now dropped on the floor. `rootCmd.Execute()` failures exit with status 1 without printing the error, so invalid workflow files, validation failures, and runtime errors become silent failures with no user-visible explanation.",
       "fix": "Print the returned error before exiting, e.g. `if err := rootCmd.Execute(); err != nil { fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"agent-runner: %v\\n\", err); os.Exit(1) }`.",
       "priority": "medium",
-      "status": "new"
+      "status": "fixed",
+      "result": "Added fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr) before os.Exit(1) to print the error"
     }
   ]
 }
